<plot>'P.A.T.H.' (which stands for Preserving, Archiving and Teaching Hip-Hop History) documents the Hip-Hop Academy, the first ever summer camp of it's kind in Miami. During the four week camp, teenagers from ages 13-18 studied Hip-Hop history, the art of deejaying, emceeing (rapping), B-boying and B-girling (break-dancing), and urban art.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?419364</url></doc>
